      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:168:6",
      "text": [
        " حَدُّ الْمُزْدَلِفَةِ مِنْ مُحَسِّرٍ إِلَى الْمَأْزِمَيْنِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya and someone else, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad and Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Ali Bin Al Numan, from Abdullah Bin Muskan, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘A boundary of Al-Muzdalifa is from Muhassar up to the two narrow points’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Muhammad ibn Yahya and others have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isma‘il from Ali ibn al-Nu’man ‘Abd Allah ibn Muskan forms who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘The boundaries of al-Muzdalifah are from Muhassar to al-Mazemin.’” "
        ]
      }
